-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fbm1665702720519.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fbm1665702720519.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fbm1665702720519.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fbm1665702720519\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Remove extra form feed from the end of print output.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__topic_d143132e1_d143133e1_d143134e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__p_d143135e1_d143136e1_d143137e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__section_idr_vxy_kwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d826653e59\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__table_d16646e1_d16647e1_d16648e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">client assignment files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__section_ysp_yxy_kwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d826653e105\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__p_d143144e1_d143145e1_d143146e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED</span> setting\n            prevents Uniface from printing an extra form feed at the end of a printout. An extra\n            form feed can result in an extra blank page at the end of the printed output.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fbm1665702720519__p_d143147e1_d143148e1_d143149e1\">If you omit the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED</span> setting, the default behavior is to print an\n            extra form feed.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527428\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527428\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Feb 07, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Remove extra form feed from the end of print output. $SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description The $SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED setting prevents Uniface from printing an extra form feed at the end of a printout. An extra form feed can result in an extra blank page at the end of the printed output. If you omit the $SUPPRESS_FORM_FEED setting, the default behavior is to print an extra form feed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}